<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Mould2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Mould,</orth> vb. to model, to form, to shape: <bibl n="shak. mm 5.444" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 444</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.211" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 211</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 3, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.100" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.23" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 1, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.239" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 239</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.177" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 177</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.10.29" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 10, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 4, 49</bibl>. Per. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.0." default="NO" valid="yes">III Prol. 11</bibl>. <emph>to m. up</emph> == to compose: <cit><quote>all princely graces that m. up such a mighty piece as this is,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.5.27" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 5, 27</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>